description.narrative:
LAMBDA is a national LGTBI organization that promotes constitutional and human rights of sexual minorities through awareness raising and education, advocacy and social dialogue. It was established in 2006 and operates at national level. It intends to reduce prejudice and discrimination against LGBTI, promotes the recognition and protection of equal rights for LGBTI and strengthens their self-esteem. It is an active partner that serves as a model for other organizations, in the fight against (sexual) discrimination. It already has the capacity of using ICT effectively in activism and advocacy.
On the AGIR Program, Lambda will work on Right to gender equality, freedom from gender-based violence and freedom of sexual and reproductive health and Right to social inclusion and non-discrimination of marginalised groups. Having LAMBDA in the programme ensures that marginalized and/or minority groups can also give their voice on issues related to their rights. LAMBDA is also a strategic partner in demystifyingthe issue of LGBTI in Mozambique, above all taking into consideration that it is a multicultural country where LGBTI issues have not yet gained the adequate space due to cultural prejudices. So LAMBDA will ensure that, being the only partner dealing withLGBTI issues, it can influence other CSOs and the government for the promotion, respect and fulfilment of LGBTI rights. LAMBDA provincial branches will support replication of the work at provincial level. Over the last years Lambda has influenced the Ministry of Health to introduce drugs and other consumables mostly used by the LGBTI in the list of essential drugs.

participating-org.narrative: WLSA has been in the frontline in advocacy for the passing of the safe abortion law. WLSA is also the leading organisation in the CSO Sexual and Reproductive Health Network. Under the network they influence duty bearers, other CSOs and rights holders on issues related to SRHR. WLSA is also experienced in research and the main studies they carry out are well disseminated and serve as evidence for advocacy for other CSOs. They virtual database has been used by different stakeholders including professionals, students and society in genera. In short, they are legitimate and renown as a very influencing CSOs for the the girls and women fundamental rights. WLSA will also bring added value in producing important shadow reports (e.g. CEDAW shadow report).
